RACE.FOOTNOTES: THE KHOZAN ONE brushed with an outer foe out of the gate, stalked in the three path, was under right handed urging from the five path turning into the stretch, ran on and surged between rivals inside the final furlong to get up for the win. LOOKINASSAH rated in the five path, ranged up under rousing around the far turn and tipped out to the nine path entering the lane, and rallied down the center for place. O GANGSTER tracked in the five path, was driven from the eight path into the stretch, and kept on for show. PHOBIA was held up in the four path early, angled inwards around the far turn and was coaxed from the rail into the lane, and finished evenly. RED'S REVENGE brushed with an inner foe at the start, prompted the pace in the four path, was in the three path around the far turn, bid from the six path into the stretch, but flattened out inside the final furlong and had to steady late. BLUE MAVERICK set the pace in the two path, tucked in to the rail around the far turn, was ridden from the three path into the stretch, but yielded into the final furlong. VOICE AN OPINION trailed throughout around the inside.
